&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LOCUM CONSULTANT IN OBSTETRICS AND GYNAECOLOGY &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; 10 Programmed Activities &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;York Teaching Hospital NHS Foundation Trust has an ambitious programme of service modernisation and a reputation for providing high quality services. In line with our outlook, we are now inviting applications for a locum resident consultant post, in the Obstetrics and Gynaecology team at York Hospital. This is an exciting opportunity to join the team, it is anticipated that there will be permanent Consultant posts advertised in the next 3 months.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will join a team consisting of 20 consultants, based across York and Scarborough, in the Obstetrics and Gynaecology service, which is provided to a population of approximately 800,000.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post advertised will be based at York Hospital site and include fixed resident consultant nights covering obstetrics and acute gynaecology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will involve covering labour ward, caesarean section lists, antenatal clinics, general gynaecology outpatients, general gynaecology operating and emergency gynaecology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Candidate must have a higher medical qualification and must have entry on the GMC Specialist Register via CCT (proposed CCT date must be within 6 months of the interview date), or CESR equivalent. A familiarity with issues of service organization and development would be particularly advantageous.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The recruitment programme for this position will be through an interview process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information about these posts please contact: Bekki Whisker Deputy Care Group Manager (01904 726200) or Mr Ben Adekanmi, Clinical Director (01904 725731).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates are positively encouraged to make contact for informal discussions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
